goals.question: What is the distribution of percentage of income earned by each region?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='region', y='avg_income', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of average income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(title='Region', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='total', y='pct', hue='region')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between total income and percentage of income earned by each region?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Total Income')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage of Income')
    plt.legend(title='Region')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['region', 'group']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    data_pivot = data_grouped.pivot_table(index='region', columns='group', values='count', fill_value=0)
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)

    plt.title("What is the distribution of income groups across different regions?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Region")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.legend(title="Income Group", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='total', hue='group', multiple='stack', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of total income across different income groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Total Income')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Income Group', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('region')['pct'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.pie(data_grouped['pct'], labels=data_grouped['region'], autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of percentage of income earned by each region?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(data_grouped['region'], loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
